! Changelog

|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|v0.1.31 |2026-05-26 |''Reorder kind fields via Ctrl-â†‘ / Ctrl-â†“ in the cascade.'' Field row order in the Manage-kinds drill IS the form field order (via `kind.field-keys` â†’ `jsonindexes[]`), so reordering `kind.fields` propagates to (a) the side-preview create form, (b) instances created after the move, (c) the validator's per-field iteration order. New protocol fields `ca-on-move-up` / `ca-on-move-down` (shipped in ''cascade-palette 0.0.57'') are now emitted on every field row in `kind.cascade-field-row-build` â€” both transclude a new `\procedure kind.cascade-move-field(target-tid, idx, dir)` that swaps `kind.fields[idx]` with `kind.fields[idx+dir]` via two chained `jsonset:json` calls (using `jsonextract<idx>` to grab each element as a JSON object, then setting them at swapped positions). ''Bounds:'' a `<$list>` guards `0 <= other-idx < count` via `compare:integer:gteq[0]` + `+[!compare:integer:gteq<count>]` â€” Ctrl-â†‘ on the top row and Ctrl-â†“ on the bottom row are silent no-ops; cp's pre-bumped selectedIndex stays clamped within the unchanged stage. ''Stream-fields unaffected:'' `kind.stream-fields` is a separate, curated ordering for the inline bar â€” moving a field in `kind.fields` does NOT also reorder it in `kind.stream-fields` (use the dedicated text-edit row for that). ''Gesture choice:'' Ctrl-â†‘/â†“ rather than Alt or Shift â€” Ctrl is already the cascade's preview-detail modifier and the magnitude modifier on number/date rows; reusing it for "move with arrows" keeps modifier-meaning consistent (Ctrl = "do the heavy version"). Bare â†‘/â†“ still nudge selection. ''Surface:'' works on the same field-row drill the schema editor uses â€” drill into a kind, focus a field row, Ctrl-â†‘/Ctrl-â†“. The side preview form re-renders live (via the 0.0.56 reactive refresh path) so the user sees the reordered form immediately. Requires cascade-palette â‰Ą 0.0.57. Tiddler-only â€” no restart. |
|v0.1.30 |2026-05-26 |''Live create-form preview while editing a kind in the cascade.'' Drilling into a kind (Node, Person, Task, â€¦) in the ''Manage kinds'' cascade now splits the popup 50/50 â€” the left column stays the schema editor (fields, metadata, delete) and the right column renders a live create-instance form for that kind. As the user adds/removes fields, changes `typed`, edits the `kind.title-formula`, tweaks `kind.caption` / `kind.icon`, etc., the side pane re-renders so the form mirrors the live schema. ''Wiring:'' uses the side-preview protocol introduced in ''cascade-palette 0.0.52'' â€” `kind.cascade-manage-kind-build` now emits two extra JSON fields on each per-kind drill row: `ca-preview-template: $:/plugins/rimir/kind/palette/preview/kind-form` and `ca-preview-title: Create form preview`. Default `ca-preview-context` (`<<picked>>`) carries the kind-tid into the template. ''Template'' (new `palette/preview/kind-form.tid`) takes the type-def tiddler as `<<currentTiddler>>`, derives `type-key` via `[get[kind.type]]`, allocates a per-kind preview-draft tiddler at `$:/state/rimir/kind/cascade-preview-draft/<type-key>` (each kind gets its own preview draft â€” switching kinds keeps each preview's in-progress values), and `$transclude`s the shared `$:/plugins/rimir/kind/editor` exactly the way `creator.tid` does (same two-column form, same field-input dispatch, same engine-import). Computed-title hint at the bottom uses `kind.eval-title` against the preview draft so the user sees what the formula resolves to as they edit it. ''Re-render trigger:'' the cp side-preview cache is keyed by (depth, context-tiddler, template) and invalidated by the wiki change hook on those two tiddlers; editing the kind type-def via any cascade row mutates the kind-tid â†’ cache invalidates â†’ form re-renders. ''Interactive form:'' the user can ALSO type values directly into the preview's input widgets â€” those values land on the per-kind preview-draft and persist across drill-in/out (until the user pops back to the kinds list, which clears the cache but not the draft tiddler â€” so re-drilling restores the values). Use it as a scratch-pad to feel out the form before committing to an actual create flow. ''No JS, no restart'' â€” tiddler-only, plus the JS engine work already shipped in cp 0.0.56. Requires cascade-palette â‰Ą 0.0.52. |
|v0.1.29 |2026-05-26 |''`k` leader: drill straight into Manage kinds.'' New leader tiddler `palette/leaders/manage-kinds.tid` (`ca-leader-key: k`) fires `<$action-sendmessage $message="rimir-cascade-palette-open-entry" entry="$:/plugins/rimir/kind/palette/entries/manage-kinds"/>` â€” single keystroke after Ctrl-Space drops the user into the Manage-kinds drill (list of kinds + "+ Create new kind" row), skipping the find-the-entry step at the root. Reuses the new `OPEN_ENTRY_MESSAGE` shipped in ''cascade-palette 0.0.54''. Works from any cp state â€” the message handler resets cp to root then drills. ''Why a leader rather than a plain entry shortcut:'' the leader subsystem already handles the after-Ctrl-Space key gesture + the pill row on the cp surface, so this re-uses existing UX. ''Listed in pill row:'' the leader's `ca-leader-name`/`ca-leader-hint`/`ca-leader-help` show up in the leader pill row + detail pane, so the gesture is discoverable. Requires cascade-palette â‰Ą 0.0.54 for the `OPEN_ENTRY_MESSAGE` handler. Tiddler-only on the kind side. |
|v0.1.28 |2026-05-26 |''Cross-link from instance â†’ kind schema editor.'' New entity action `actions/edit-kind-schema.tid` (`ca-entity-type: kind-entity`, đź§°, order 60 â€” between Edit fields and Delete) drills directly into the type-def's Manage-kinds stage from any kind-typed instance, skipping the Ctrl-Space â†’ Manage kinds â†’ find-the-right-kind detour. ''How:'' the action's `ca-items-from` calls a new helper `kind.cascade-edit-kind-schema-items(entity-tid)` which (1) reads the entity's `kind.type` field, (2) resolves to its type-def tiddler via `kind.locate-type`, (3) emits the same edit rows the Manage-kinds drill uses via `kind.cascade-kind-edit-items`. The middle `:map`/`:map:flat` distinction is deliberate â€” `locate-type` returns one type-tid per kind.type input so plain `:map` works, but `cascade-kind-edit-items` returns N rows per type-tid so the second hop needs `:map:flat` (per the [[tw-gotchas-filters#`:map` returns only the FIRST]] gotcha). ''Surface:'' any cp flow that exposes kind-entity instances (Find entity, Find by kind â†’ kind â†’ instances) now offers Edit kind schema in the action menu; Right-arrow â†’ â†“ to Edit kind schema â†’ Enter drops into the schema editor for that exact kind, no detour. Symmetric with the existing Open / Edit fields / Delete kind-entity actions. ''Edge:'' if the entity has no `kind.type` or the type-def doesn't exist, the drill returns nothing (empty stage); the action menu doesn't pre-filter for this â€” the row is offered for any kind-entity, which is fine because the actual kind-entity entity-type marker is only set on stages that legitimately have kind.type instances. Tiddler-only â€” no restart. |
|v0.1.27 |2026-05-26 |''Fix: `:map[X]` silently drops every result past index 0; cross-kind option pool was returning ~1 value instead of N.'' Looking at TW core's `filterrunprefixes/map.js:33` â€” without the `:flat` suffix, `:map[X]` pushes ONLY `filtered[0]||""` per iteration: the FIRST result of the inner filter, or empty string if it returned nothing. So when `:map` calls a function that returns multiple titles per iteration, all but the first are lost. ''Impact in the options picker:'' four cascade points each lost their tails â€” `kind.cascade-field-options-picker-items` :map'd `cascade-options-picker-with-key` (5 toggles + add-row â†’ kept only first toggle), `kind.options-from-all-kinds` :map'd `options-from-kind` per kind (multi-option fields â†’ kept only first option per kind), `kind.options-from-common-fields` :map'd `cf-options-at-cf-tid` per common-field (multi-option defs â†’ kept only first option per cf), `kind.options-from-kind` :map'd `options-at-idx` per field-idx (multi-option arrays â†’ kept only first option per idx). End result: pool collapsed to 1-2 values and the add-row was always dropped (because the function returned multiple items and only the first toggle survived). ''Fix:'' all four call sites switched to `:map:flat[function[NAME],...]` which iterates `$tw.utils.each(filtered, â€¦)` instead of `filtered[0]`. With `:flat`, every result from each iteration's inner filter is appended. Pool now correctly produces the full union; add-row now reaches cascade-palette. ''Lesson:'' use `:map:flat` whenever the inner filter (typically a `function[NAME]` call) returns more than one value per input â€” which is most cases when wrapping multi-result helpers. `:map` (no flat) is the right default ONLY when the inner filter is guaranteed to emit exactly one value per input (e.g., simple value extractors `:map[get[caption]]`). Tiddler-only â€” no restart. |
|v0.1.26 |2026-05-25 |''Fix: enum options picker now also includes library common-field options + filters blanks.'' Two fixes to 0.1.25's cross-kind option pool. ''(a) Common-fields integration:'' the pool was only walking `kind.types-all` (user-defined kinds) â€” the shadow common-field tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/kind/common-field` were ignored. So `task.status` (an enum) ignored the canonical `["open","active","done","archived"]` defined on `$:/plugins/rimir/kind/common-fields/status` even though that's the ship-with canonical set. ''Fix:'' added `kind.options-from-common-fields(field-key)` that iterates `kind.common-fields-all`, filters via `kind.cf-matches-enum-key` (matches def's key + typed=enum), and emits the def's options array via `kind.cf-options-at-cf-tid`. Pool now unions across-kinds AND common-fields. ''(b) Blank values pollution:'' `+[unique[]sort[]]` deduped but didn't filter empty values â€” if any source kind had an empty-string option (manual JSON edit, old serialization quirk, etc.) the pool would emit an unnamed toggle. ''Fix:'' switched the final pool reduce to `+[!is[blank]unique[]sort[]]`. ''Refactor:'' renamed `kind.options-pool`'s direct kind-walk to `kind.options-from-all-kinds` for parallelism with `kind.options-from-common-fields`. ''Example after fix:'' add a fresh `status` enum field to any kind â€” picker immediately shows `active`, `archived`, `done`, `open` as OFF toggles (from the common-fields canonical set) + "+ Add new optionâ€¦" â€” toggle any on to populate this field's `options` without typing. Same applies to `priority` (`low`, `medium`, `high`) and any future common-field with enum + options. Tiddler-only â€” no restart. |
|v0.1.25 |2026-05-25 |''Cross-kind option pool for enum picker.'' Options picker now suggests every option ever used on a same-named enum field across all kinds, not just the ones currently set on this field. Pool computed by `kind.options-pool(field-key)`: walks `kind.types-all`, for each kind iterates its `kind.fields` indices, filters to those whose `key` matches the current field-key AND whose `typed` is `enum`, collects each matching field's `options` values, then `+[unique[]sort[]]`. Each pool value becomes a toggle row â€” cascade-palette's existing toggle widget renders it ON if the value is in THIS field's `options` array, OFF otherwise (same mechanic ref-types uses). User can toggle pool members on/off without re-typing them; "+ Add new optionâ€¦" still appends a fresh option that automatically joins the pool for that field-key in other kinds. ''Example:'' kind `task` has field `priority` with options `["low","high"]`; kind `meeting` adds field `priority` (enum); picker on meeting.priority shows `low` + `high` as OFF toggles + "+ Add new optionâ€¦" â€” toggle them on without typing. ''New helpers:'' `kind.cascade-options-picker-with-key` (intermediate to thread field-key), `kind.options-pool`, `kind.options-from-kind`, `kind.field-matches-enum-key`, `kind.options-at-idx`. Picker entry now resolves field-key first (`jsonget<field-idx>,[key]` with `~[[]]` fallback so blank-key fields still get the add-option row). ''Why no special-case for ad-hoc empty pool:'' a brand-new enum field's pool may be empty (no other kind has a same-named enum field yet) â€” that's fine, picker just shows the add-row and the first option entered seeds the pool for future same-named fields. Cross-kind pooling is name-based; renaming a field changes which pool it draws from. Tiddler-only â€” no restart. |
|v0.1.24 |2026-05-25 |''Multi-pick sub-stage for enum options + shared array-append helper.'' Enum `options` previously was a flat text-edit row binding the whole array via `ca-bind-type: application/x-string-array` (one space-separated string the user re-typed wholesale). Now it's a drill into a picker that lists each existing option as a toggle row (toggle off = remove that option from the array) plus a "+ Add new optionâ€¦" text row at the bottom that appends a new value via a shared procedure. Same UX shape as the constraints picker â€” Space drills, options become individually toggleable, new ones added one-at-a-time with dedup. ''Refactor:'' `kind.cascade-append-constraint` is gone â€” its body now lives in the generic `kind.cascade-append-array-value(target-tid, idx, prop, value)` procedure (one extra `prop` parameter threaded into `jsonindexes<idx>,<prop>` / `jsonget<idx>,<prop>,<currentTiddler>` / `jsonset:json<idx>,<prop>,<new-array>`). Custom-constraint row and add-option row both transclude the generic helper, passing `prop="constraints"` or `prop="options"`. No code duplication â€” same dedup-via-unique + quote-string + join + wrap-array + empty-array-fallback pipeline serves both. Dead helper `kind.cascade-field-array-prop-row` (the old wholesale text-edit array binder) removed â€” last caller was the old options-row. New helpers: `kind.cascade-field-options-picker-items`, `kind.cascade-field-add-option-row`. ''ref-types'' already drilled into a multi-pick picker (all kind types as toggles since 0.1.11) â€” no change. Tiddler-only â€” no restart. |
|v0.1.23 |2026-05-25 |''Fix: min/max constraint write was still buggy in 0.1.22 â€” subtract-of-existing didn't fire, validity filter let everything through.'' Two more bugs in the min/max constraint path. ''(a) `-[prefix<prefix>]` didn't subtract:'' the run-prefix-`-` semantics: subtract the INNER run's output from the accumulator. The inner expression `[prefix<prefix>]` has no explicit input source â€” TW filter parser then uses the default source (all tiddlers + shadows) rather than the accumulator, so `prefix<prefix>` returned wiki titles starting with "min:" (typically none), and subtract removed nothing. Works fine when the inner is a literal value (`-[<del-idx>]` in `kind.rebuilt-fields-without`) because that emits the variable's value directly without needing a source. ''Fix:'' switched to `:filter[<currentTiddler>!prefix<prefix>]` â€” `:filter` iterates the accumulator setting `<currentTiddler>` per item, so the predicate operates on each constraint value individually. Now `"5"` correctly replaces `"min:3"` with `"min:5"` (no leftover). ''(b) `compare:integer:gteq[0]` accepted "abc":'' TW's `parseInt("abc")` returns `NaN`. The compare gtFn returns `0` (default branch, NaN <-> NaN comparisons all false), `gteq` treats `r===0` as true. So `"abc" compare:integer:gteq[0]` evaluates to TRUE â€” non-numeric input passed the validity filter and reached the rewrite as `"min:abc"`. Conversely the previous fix `[<value>match[]]` for the blank case relied on `<value>` substitution producing `[""]` for empty value, but TW substitutes empty variables to NO INPUT (not empty string) â€” so `match[]` had no source and blank input was REJECTED. ''Fix:'' switched to `[<value>] ~[[]] +[is[blank]] [<value>regexp{$:/plugins/rimir/kind/_patterns!!digits}] +[first[]]` â€” the `~[[]]` fallback explicitly provides empty string as a result when `<value>` substitutes nothing, then `+[is[blank]]` keeps it (clear semantics); separately `[<value>regexp{...digits}]` adds the value if it matches `^[0-9]+$`; `+[first[]]` coalesces. Non-numeric / non-blank input produces no filter result â†’ list doesn't iterate â†’ action skipped â†’ existing constraint stays. New `digits` pattern added to `_patterns.tid` (referenced via textref so the `[0-9]` character class doesn't break filter parsing â€” same trick as 0.1.21's email/phone patterns). ''Lessons:'' (1) `-[op<arg>]` only subtracts correctly when the inner is a value-emission (literal / variable); for operator-based subtraction use `:filter[<currentTiddler>!op<arg>]` to bind the accumulator as input. (2) `<v>` substitution with empty value produces no filter input â€” use `~[[]]` fallback explicitly. (3) `compare:integer` treats NaN as equal-to-anything (returns 0 from gtFn); never trust it for numeric input validation â€” use `regexp` with a stored pattern instead. Tiddler-only â€” no restart. |
|v0.1.22 |2026-05-25 |''Fix: setting min/max constraint via cascade prefixed all existing constraints, not just the new one.'' Two related bugs in `kind.computed-constraints-with-valid-picked` + `kind.cascade-set-constraint-num`. ''(a) Chain-prefix bug:'' the new-entry branch was written as `[<valid-picked>!is[blank]] +[addprefix<prefix>]` â€” two separate filter runs. The first accumulated `picked` ("3") onto the already-filtered list ("required"), giving ["required", "3"]. The `+[addprefix<prefix>]` then operated on the FULL accumulator (TW filter `+` prefix = "pipe accumulator through op"), prepending "min:" to BOTH entries â†’ ["min:required", "min:3"]. If the user (mis-)typed the full prefixed form like "min:3" thinking they had to retype the label, the result included a "min:min:3" entry. ''Fix:'' inlined `addprefix<prefix>` into the same operator chain as the new-entry emit: `[<valid-picked>!is[blank]addprefix<prefix>]`. Now the prefix is only applied to the new entry, not the entire accumulator. ''(b) Regex validity guard didn't validate:'' the procedure's outer `<$list filter="[<value>regexp[^[0-9]*$]]">` tried to reject non-digit input but the pattern `^[0-9]*$` contains a `]` inside the bracket-counting filter parser, breaking the regex parse and effectively passing ALL input through. So "min:3" / "abc" / etc. reached the rewrite. ''Fix:'' switched to `<$list filter="[<value>match[]] [<value>compare:integer:gteq[0]] +[first[]]">` â€” `match[]` matches the blank value (clear semantics), `compare:integer:gteq[0]` matches any non-negative integer, +[first[]] coalesces. Non-digit / invalid input now produces an empty filter result, the action no-ops, and the existing constraint stays intact. ''Lesson:'' for TW regex patterns containing `]`, store the pattern in a separate tiddler field and reference via textref `{$:/.../patterns!!name}` â€” the textref is substituted before bracket-counting (same workaround the 0.1.21 url/email/phone work uses for `[^@\s]`). For simple ranges, prefer the `compare:integer:gteq` / `match[]` combo â€” brackets-free. Still open: cascade-palette text-edit row's right-side "(unset)" display for unbound rows is purely cosmetic (the actual value is shown in `ca-name` as "min: 3"); needs a cp engine change to suppress the bound-value column when no bind is declared. Tiddler-only â€” no restart. |
|v0.1.21 |2026-05-25 |''Three new field-types with intrinsic format validation: `url` / `email` / `phone`.'' All three are text-like single-line inputs with HTML5 input semantics (`type="url"` / `type="email"` / `type="tel"` â€” browser-native hints, mobile-keyboard hints on tel). ''`url'':'' checked for `http://` or `https://` prefix via two chained `!prefix` ops on the field value. ''`email'':'' checked via regex `^[^@\s]+@[^@\s]+\.[^@\s]+$` (non-empty local, non-empty domain, â‰Ą1 dot, no whitespace, no extra `@`). ''`phone'':'' checked via regex `^(\+49|0)[ 0-9()\/\-]{6,}$` for German numbers (starts with `+49` or `0`, â‰Ą6 allowed chars after). ''Regex storage pattern:'' new `_patterns.tid` holds the email + phone-de patterns as FIELDS, referenced via textref `{$:/plugins/rimir/kind/_patterns!!<name>}` â€” the textref form is substituted by the parser BEFORE bracket-counting, so the `[^@\s]` character classes in the patterns don't break filter parsing (see [[tw-gotchas-parser-pragma#Backtick-template operand]]). URL check doesn't need a `_patterns` entry â€” `!prefix[http://]!prefix[https://]` is brackets-free. ''Engine:'' three new viol predicates `kind.viol-format-url` / `-email` / `-phone` (each fires only when typed matches AND value non-blank â€” the existing `required` constraint still handles the empty case independently). All three added to `kind.viol-any` so they block Create in the creator and surface in the validator. `kind.minmax-applicable` extended to include url/email/phone â€” `min:N` / `max:N` now constrain character length on these too. ''Field-input:'' three new dispatch branches in the `<%elseif%>` cascade with HTML5 input types and placeholders (`https://â€¦`, `name@example.com`, `+49 30 12345678`). Three new validation error messages below the input (next to the existing required/min/max/unique/unique:wiki ones). ''Validator:'' three new bulk-report rows with the offending value shown in the detail column. ''Type-builder:'' `<$select>` typed dropdown gains the three new options; `th` tooltip + Raw JSON schema help text updated. ''Cascade-palette:'' three new `try-shape-*` branches in `cascade-helpers.tid` (route through `shape-text-with-typed` â€” cascade rows are single-line text; live format errors only surface in the regular editor, not in cascade-mode text rows). `palette/cascade-helpers.tid` typed picker (Manage kinds â†’ field drill â†’ typed) lists the three new types. ''Common-fields library:'' three new shadow tiddlers `common-fields/{url,email,phone}.tid` tagged `$:/tags/rimir/kind/common-field` â€” appear in the type-builder library dropdown AND the cascade `+ Add field from libraryâ€¦` picker. Icons: đź”— / đź“§ / đź“ž. ''Docs:'' architecture + reference doc tables list new typed values, constraint table notes the intrinsic format check, engine function table lists the new viol predicates. Tiddler-only â€” no JS, no restart. |
|v0.1.20 |2026-05-25 |''Fix: nested JSON-array reads silently returned empty.'' Five helpers built their nested-array reads as `get[kind.fields]jsonget<idx>,[prop]jsonindexes[]` and `:map[â€¦jsonget<idx>,[prop]jsonget<currentTiddler>]` (chain `jsongetâ†’jsonindexes` / `jsongetâ†’jsonget`). The chain returned nothing in practice â€” even though `jsonget<idx>,[prop]` does produce the inner array's JSON string and `jsonindexes[]` should parse it, in the filter chain it always read as empty. ''Symptom:'' the min/max rows in the constraints picker showed "(none)" for fields with `constraints:["required","min:3"]` even though the bound-drill preview on the parent showed `min:3` correctly; 0.1.17 enum-no-options / ref-no-reftypes hints were also emitted whenever typed=enum / typed=ref regardless of actual options / ref-types presence. ''Fix:'' switched to the canonical pattern from `engine.tid:22` (`kind.field-array-flat`): `jsonindexes<idx>,[prop]` walks the path AND returns the indices in one operator; `jsonget<idx>,[prop],<currentTiddler>` reads each value via three-arg path navigation. ''Affected helpers'' (all in `palette/cascade-helpers.tid`): `kind.cascade-current-constraint-num`, `kind.computed-constraints-with-valid-picked`, `kind.cascade-append-constraint` (inline filter inside the procedure), `kind.cascade-issue-enum-no-options`, `kind.cascade-issue-ref-no-reftypes`. After this fix: min/max rows show "min: 3" / "max: (none)" correctly; enum-no-options / ref-no-reftypes only emit when the respective array is genuinely empty. ''Lesson:'' for nested JSON-array walks in TW, never chain `jsongetâ†’jsonindexes`; use `jsonindexes<path>` with the full path in one operator. Tiddler-only â€” no restart. |
|v0.1.19 |2026-05-25 |''Parameterised constraints (`min:N` / `max:N` / custom) in the constraints picker.'' The constraints sub-stage previously offered only the three flag-constraints `required` / `unique` / `unique:wiki` (as toggle rows). Three new rows extend it: two text-edit rows ''min'' (â‰Ą, order 100) and ''max'' (â‰¤, order 110) that capture a non-negative integer and write it as `min:N` / `max:N` into the field's `constraints` JSON array, plus a ''+ Add custom constraintâ€¦'' (âśš, order 200) text-edit row that appends any user-typed string (e.g. `regex:[a-z]+`) to the array. ''min/max applicability:'' rows only render when `kind.minmax-applicable` passes â€” typed is text/longtext/number/date/datetime OR cardinality is multi (same gate the engine's `kind.viol-min` / `viol-max` use). ''Custom applicability:'' renders whenever `kind.required-applicable` passes (typed not $title/$calculated/blank). ''Current value surfaced'' in min/max `ca-name`: "min: 5" / "max: (none)" â€” the row's name updates on every render via `kind.cascade-current-constraint-num` which reads existing constraints, filters by prefix, strips prefix, takes first. ''Set semantics:'' the `\procedure kind.cascade-set-constraint-num(target-tid, idx, prefix, value)` filter-rejects non-digit input via `<$list filter="[<value>regexp[^[0-9]*$]]">` (typos silently no-op â€” old value retained); blank input clears the constraint (removes the prefix:* entry); digit input replaces (removes old prefix:* and adds new prefix:value, dedup-safe). The new array is rebuilt via `kind.computed-constraints-with-valid-picked` â€” fetches all constraint values, subtracts those starting with prefix, optionally appends the new prefix:value, quotes each via `kind.quote-string`, joins with commas, wraps in [ ] via `kind.wrap-array`; empty result falls back to `kind.empty-array`. Written via `jsonset:json<idx>,[constraints],<new-array>` against `kind.fields`. ''Append semantics:'' `\procedure kind.cascade-append-constraint(target-tid, idx, value)` appends value to the existing array with `+[unique[]]` dedup; same rebuild + jsonset:json pattern. ''Explicit `value` parameter'' on both procedures (rather than relying on `<picked>` scope inheritance) â€” the row's on-commit transclude passes `value=<<picked>>`. ''Why text-edit rather than drill into a sub-picker:'' min/max are open-ended integers â€” a picker would need to enumerate values; text-edit is more natural. Custom is open-ended by design. ''Toggle picker still shows current state'' for required / unique / unique:wiki, so the constraints sub-stage now has a mix of toggle + text rows in one picker â€” cascade-palette routes Space/Enter per-row by `ca-kind`. ''Deletion of custom constraints'' is not yet supported in cascade â€” user edits `kind.fields` JSON directly via the type-builder tab (or via the `constraints` text-edit row that takes the whole space-separated list when typed=array). New helpers: `kind.cascade-field-minmax-row`, `kind.cascade-minmax-row-with-value`, `kind.cascade-constraint-num-row-build`, `kind.cascade-minmax-applicable-here`, `kind.cascade-minmax-applicable-with-typed`, `kind.cascade-current-constraint-num`, `kind.cascade-field-custom-constraint-row`, `kind.cascade-custom-constraint-row-build`, `kind.computed-constraints-with-valid-picked`. New procedures: `kind.cascade-set-constraint-num`, `kind.cascade-append-constraint`. Requires cascade-palette â‰Ą 0.0.53 for `ca-on-commit`. Tiddler-only â€” no restart. |
